{"id": "EUVD-2025-11246", "enisaUuid": "c972830a-ed06-3fcf-a078-d1320c77058d", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nksmbd: fix overflow in dacloffset bounds check\n\nThe dacloffset field was originally typed as int and used in an\nunchecked addition, which could overflow and bypass the existing\nbounds check in both smb_check_perm_dacl() and smb_inherit_dacl().\n\nThis could result in out-of-bounds memory access and a kernel crash\nwhen dereferencing the DACL pointer.\n\nThis patch converts dacloffset to unsigned int and uses\ncheck_add_overflow() to validate access to the DACL.", "datePublished": "2025-04-16T15:34:40", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-14T18:31:18", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-22039", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/443b373a4df5a2cb9f7b8c4658b2afedeb16397f", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/6a9cd9ff0fa2bcc30b2bfb8bdb161eb20e44b9dc", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/6b8d379048b168a0dff5ab1acb975b933f368514", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/beff0bc9d69bc8e733f9bca28e2d3df5b3e10e42"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-22039", "GHSA-xm3p-r4jv-jxcf"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.01, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "42035383-dbef-3f6b-9a24-c4aceef0b27b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <443b373a4df5a2cb9f7b8c4658b2afedeb16397f"}, {"id": "47233abf-96bd-35db-8e3a-fc20c18844a1", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.15-rc1"}, {"id": "7cb6bc53-41fb-350a-be90-063eca25880c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.14.2"}, {"id": "834e1f1a-3afc-327d-bec2-adbf822b9fb5", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.13.11"}, {"id": "97afcb32-15c4-34ce-83ee-a98e4bb0717a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <beff0bc9d69bc8e733f9bca28e2d3df5b3e10e42"}, {"id": "a183e5dd-38aa-300f-bb52-522a3cf962a6", "product": {"name": "Linux"},